thread.title: Vikings finish eighth at Winnipeg volleyball tourney
thread.title_full: Vikings finish eighth at Winnipeg volleyball tourney

title: Vikings finish eighth at Winnipeg volleyball tourney
text:
Vikings finish eighth at Winnipeg volleyball tourney By: Uncredited Report Error 
The Vincent Massey Vikings varsity girls’ volleyball team finished eighth at the West Winnipeg high school tournament on the weekend. 
The Vikings, who were fourth in the provincial AAAA rankings, knocked off cross-town rival Neelin 25-23, 25-14 in the round of 16 before dropping three consecutive matches to close out the event, including straight sets losses to No. 5 Mennonite Brethren and No. 6 Fort Richmond. Neelin placed 11th at the event while Crocus Plains tied for 15th. 
Meanwhile, the Massey boys, who are ranked eighth in the province, finished ninth at the St. Vital Invitational. Matt Robinson had 13 kills and three stuff blocks while Cole Tokaryk added 11 kills and six stuff blocks as the Vikings swept the No. 9 Dakota Lancers 3-0 (25-16, 25-20, 27-25) in the ninth-place match.
